Name: munge8bit
Type: SWITCH
Default-Value: 1
Last-Modified: 2.3.17

If enabled, lmtpd munges messages with 8-bit characters in the headers.
The 8-bit characters are changed to \`X'.  If :imapdconf:`reject8bit` is
enabled, setting *munge8bit* has no effect.  (A proper solution to
non-ASCII characters in headers is offered by :rfc:`2047` and its
predecessors.)
